{
  "stem": "14060.8",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And at 11 o'clock, before much was done, because it takes time to-- they line up, they give the orders, they come out of the blocks, they stand together till they are told.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You know, it doesn't happen in minutes. 11 o'clock, the air raid sirens went.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Everything stopped.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "What was known to us was that about 12 on the clock, we saw the American tanks about 500 meters outside the camp on the main road driving along.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "What became apparent-- and a true story-- was that the Germans ran away between 10:00 and 11:00 in the morning from-- from-- from Buchenwald to Weimar.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They mined most of the camp-- or all of it, I don't know for sure-- and left a few odd guards just for show, so to speak, and gave them instructions to blow up the camp.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That's how precisely even at that stage, 11 of April.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The war was over in less than a month.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Anyway, luckily the-- there were a large group of Russian prisoners of war which were of military age, and they were used to roughing it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They were not like civilians coming out of school and then [INAUDIBLE] homes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they got wind of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They overpowered those few guards who were left there in the intervening hours between the time the main lot of SS left and the Americans were seen to arrive.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they got a telephone call-- I don't know exactly the time-- apparently some time between 11:30, 12 o'clock, something like that, has the plan been carried out?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They said yes, which meant the-- the camp in the main part has been destroyed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that is the story.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was about 21,000, 23,000 people who were liberated in Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, it was a very large camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
